        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Cantharellus anzutake a, b Ka & Ryoo 3 _ Korea _ 1 - 2 [22 / 08 / 2012, Pyeongchang, Jungwangsan, 37 ° 27 ' 27.48 \" N, 128 ° 29 ' 04.35 \" E, 771 m asl, under Pinus koraiensis Siebold & Zucc.] c Antonin 16.140 (PC 0142465). Note the very pale hymenophore in young specimens, remaining for a long time paler closer to the stipe when maturing. Scale bar: 20 mm." , "Figure 8. Cantharellus anzutake. Microscopic features. Basidia, basidiola and spores. Scale bar: 10 μm, but only 5 μm for spores. Drawings B. Buyck." , "Figure 7. Cantharellus anzutake, microscopic features. Hyphal extremities at the pileus surface, on the left near the pileus center, on the right closer to the pileus margin. Scale bar: 10 μm. Drawings B. Buyck." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489865" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489864" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489863" .

